3.5 Forecast performance

# Find all combinations of Store_ID, Article_No og dates from dfUDF
all_combinations <- expand_grid(
  Store_ID = unique(dfUDF$Store_ID),
  Article_No = unique(dfUDF$Article_No),
  Date = unique(dfUDF$Date)
)
all_combinations <- all_combinations %>% 
  filter(Date <= "2025-04-27") #remove dates where actual sales doesn't exist


# Join with dfSales og insert 0 for Net_Sales_Pcs, if missing data
dfSales_filled <- all_combinations %>%
  left_join(dfSales, by = c("Store_ID", "Article_No", "Date")) %>%
  mutate(Net_Sales_Pcs = ifelse(is.na(Net_Sales_Pcs), 0, Net_Sales_Pcs))

# Join dfSales and dfUDF by Date
dfCompare <- inner_join(dfSales_filled, dfUDF, 
                        by = c("Store_ID", "Article_No", "Date"))

# Calculate metrics
dfCompare <- dfCompare %>%
  mutate(
    Forecast = fct,
    Actual = as.numeric(Net_Sales_Pcs),
    Error = Forecast - Actual,
    AbsError = abs(Error),
    SquaredError = Error^2,
    APE = ifelse(Actual != 0, abs(Error) / Actual, NA), # Avoid div-by-zero
    sAPE = ifelse((abs(Forecast) + abs(Actual)) == 0, 0,
                  abs(Forecast - Actual) / ((abs(Forecast) + abs(Actual)) / 2))
  )

# Performance metrics
performance_summary <- dfCompare %>%
  summarise(
    MFE = mean(Error, na.rm = TRUE), # Mean Forecast Error
    MAE = mean(AbsError, na.rm = TRUE), # Mean Absolute Error
    RMSE = sqrt(mean(SquaredError, na.rm = TRUE)), # Root Mean Squared Error
    MAPE = mean(APE, na.rm = TRUE) * 100, # Mean Absolute Percentage Error
    sMAPE = mean(sAPE, na.rm = TRUE) * 100 # Symmetric Mean Absolute Percentage Error
  )

knitr::kable(performance_summary,
 caption = "Forecast performance summary")

MFE MAE RMSE MAPE sMAPE

4.3 Calculate distribution statistics

df_stats <- dfUDF %>%
  group_by(Article_No, Store_ID) %>%
  summarise(
    Mean_Demand = sum(fct, na.rm = TRUE),
    n_days = n(),  # days
    .groups = "drop"
  ) %>%
  left_join(dfSD, by = c("Article_No", "Store_ID")) %>%
  mutate(
    Std_Demand = SD_Error * sqrt(n_days),  # total SD
    cX = Std_Demand / Mean_Demand,      # coefficient of variation
    a = cX^2 - 1 / Mean_Demand
  )

4.4 Distribution Classification

# Fit distribution and parameters
fit_distribution <- function(df) {
  df <- df %>%
    mutate(
      # Classify distributions based on 'a'
      distribution = case_when(
        abs(a) < 0.001 ~ "Poisson",  # Poisson if a is very close to 0
        a < 0 ~ "Mixture of Binomials",  # Mixture of Binomials if a is negative
        a > 0 & a < 1 ~ "Mixture of Negative Binomials",  # Mixture of Negative Binomials if a is between 0 and 1
        a >= 1 ~ "Mixture of Geometrics",  # Mixture of Geometrics if a > 1
        TRUE ~ "Unclassified"
      ),
      
      # Calculate k based on distribution
      k = case_when(
        distribution == "Mixture of Binomials" ~ floor(-1 / a),  # For Mixture of Binomials (a is negative)
        distribution == "Mixture of Negative Binomials" ~ floor(1 / a),  # For Mixture of Negative Binomials (a is positive and less than 1)
        TRUE ~ NA_real_
      ),
      
      # Parameters for Poisson
      lambda = case_when(
        distribution == "Poisson" ~ Mean_Demand,
        TRUE ~ NA_real_
      ),
      
      # Parameters for Mixture of Binomials
      q_binomial = case_when(
        distribution == "Mixture of Binomials" ~ pmax(0, pmin(1, (1 + a * (1 + k) + sqrt(-a * k * (1 + k) - k)) / (1 + a))), # Min 0, Max 1
        TRUE ~ NA_real_
      ),
      p_binomial = case_when(
        distribution == "Mixture of Binomials" ~ pmax(0, pmin(1, Mean_Demand / (k + 1 - q_binomial))), # Min 0, Max 1
        TRUE ~ NA_real_
      ),
      
      # Parameters for Mixture of Negative Binomials
      q_neg_binomial = case_when(
        distribution == "Mixture of Negative Binomials" ~ pmax(0, pmin(1, ((1 + k) * a - sqrt((1 + k) * (1 - a * k))) / (1 + a)) ), # Min 0, Max 1
        TRUE ~ NA_real_
      ),
      p_neg_binomial = case_when(
        distribution == "Mixture of Negative Binomials" ~ pmax(0, pmin(1, Mean_Demand / (k + 1 - q_neg_binomial + Mean_Demand))), # Min 0, Max 1
        TRUE ~ NA_real_
      ),
      
      # Parameters for Mixture of Geometrics
      p1_geom = case_when(
        distribution == "Mixture of Geometrics" ~ Mean_Demand * (1 + a + sqrt(a^2 - 1)) / (2 + Mean_Demand * (1 + a + sqrt(a^2 - 1))),
        TRUE ~ NA_real_
      ),
      p2_geom = case_when(
        distribution == "Mixture of Geometrics" ~ Mean_Demand * (1 + a - sqrt(a^2 - 1)) / (2 + Mean_Demand * (1 + a - sqrt(a^2 - 1))),
        TRUE ~ NA_real_
      ),
      q1_geom = case_when(
        distribution == "Mixture of Geometrics" ~ 1 / (1 + a + sqrt(a^2 - 1)),
        TRUE ~ NA_real_
      ),
      q2_geom = case_when(
        distribution == "Mixture of Geometrics" ~ 1 / (1 + a - sqrt(a^2 - 1)),
        TRUE ~ NA_real_
      )
    )
  
  return(df)
}

5.2 Load allocation heuristic

allocate_units <- function(df, total_units = 1000, simulations = 1000, gain_cutoff = 1e-6) {
  
  df$allocated <- 0  # Reset allocation column
  total_expected_gain <- 0 
  
  # Expected sales gain from next colli
  expected_sales_gain <- function(i, current_units) {
    dist <- df$distribution[i]
    mu <- df$Mean_Demand[i]
    colli <- df$Colli_Size[i]
    stock_now <- current_units
    stock_next <- current_units + colli
    
    if (dist == "Poisson") {
      lambda <- df$lambda[i]
      demand <- rpois(simulations, lambda)
      
    } else if (dist == "Mixture of Binomials") {
      k <- df$k[i]
      q <- df$q_binomial[i]
      p <- df$p_binomial[i]
      demand <- ifelse(runif(simulations) < q,
                       rbinom(simulations, k, p),
                       rbinom(simulations, k + 1, p))
      
    } else if (dist == "Mixture of Negative Binomials") {
      k <- df$k[i]
      q <- df$q_neg_binomial[i]
      demand <- ifelse(runif(simulations) < q,
                       rnbinom(simulations, size = k, mu = mu),
                       rnbinom(simulations, size = k + 1, mu = mu))
      
    } else if (dist == "Mixture of Geometrics") {
      p1 <- df$p1_geom[i]
      p2 <- df$p2_geom[i]
      q1 <- df$q1_geom[i]
      demand <- ifelse(runif(simulations) < q1,
                       rgeom(simulations, p1),
                       rgeom(simulations, p2))
      
    } else {
      return(0)
    }
    
    sold_now <- pmin(demand, stock_now)
    sold_next <- pmin(demand, stock_next)
    
    return(mean(sold_next - sold_now))  # Expected gain from next colli
  }
  
  # Step 1: Fill presentation stock (minimum stock level)
  for (i in seq_len(nrow(df))) {
    coverage <- df$Stock[i] + df$Open_Order_Qty[i]
    shortage <- df$Min_Stock[i] - coverage
    
    if (shortage > 0) {
      colli <- df$Colli_Size[i]
      required_colli <- ceiling(shortage / colli)
      allocate_now <- min(required_colli * colli, total_units)
      df$allocated[i] <- allocate_now
      total_units <- total_units - allocate_now
    }
  }
  
  # Step 2: Greedy allocation using expected sales gain
  repeat {
    current_stock <- df$Stock + df$Open_Order_Qty + df$allocated
    raw_gains <- sapply(1:nrow(df), function(i) expected_sales_gain(i, current_stock[i]))
    
    best_gain <- max(raw_gains)
    if (best_gain < gain_cutoff) {
      message("No significant expected sales gain. Stopping allocation.")
      break
    }
    
    if (total_units < min(df$Colli_Size)) {
      message("Not enough units left to allocate a full colli. Stopping allocation.")
      break
    }
    
    best_index <- which.max(raw_gains)
    colli <- df$Colli_Size[best_index]
    
    if (total_units >= colli) {
      df$allocated[best_index] <- df$allocated[best_index] + colli
      total_units <- total_units - colli
      
      total_expected_gain <- total_expected_gain + best_gain

    } else {
      break
    }
  }
  
  message("Total expected increase in sales from allocation: ", round(total_expected_gain, 2))
  return(df)
}

6.2 Simulatation for OOS situations

simulate_oos <- function(df, simulations = 1000) {
  oos_results <- numeric(simulations)
  
  for (sim in 1:simulations) {
    simulated_demand <- numeric(nrow(df))
    
    for (i in seq_len(nrow(df))) {
      dist <- df$distribution[i]
      
      if (dist == "Poisson") {
        simulated_demand[i] <- rpois(1, lambda = df$lambda[i])
        
      } else if (dist == "Mixture of Binomials") {
        k <- df$k[i]
        q <- df$q_binomial[i]
        p <- df$p_binomial[i]
        
        # Simulate from mixture
        if (runif(1) < q) {
          simulated_demand[i] <- rbinom(1, size = k, prob = p)
        } else {
          simulated_demand[i] <- rbinom(1, size = k + 1, prob = p)
        }
        
      } else if (dist == "Mixture of Negative Binomials") {
        k <- df$k[i]
        q <- df$q_neg_binomial[i]
        p <- df$p_neg_binomial[i]
        mu <- df$Mean_Demand[i]
        
        # Simulate from mixture
        if (runif(1) < q) {
          simulated_demand[i] <- rnbinom(1, size = k, mu = mu)
        } else {
          simulated_demand[i] <- rnbinom(1, size = k + 1, mu = mu)
        }
        
      } else if (dist == "Mixture of Geometrics") {
        p1 <- df$p1_geom[i]
        p2 <- df$p2_geom[i]
        q1 <- df$q1_geom[i]
        q2 <- df$q2_geom[i]
        
        mix_draw <- runif(1)
        if (mix_draw < q1) {
          simulated_demand[i] <- rgeom(1, prob = p1)
        } else {
          simulated_demand[i] <- rgeom(1, prob = p2)
        }
          
      } else {
        stop(paste("Unknown distribution:", dist))
      }
    }
    
    available_stock <- df$Stock + df$Open_Order_Qty + df$allocated
    oos_results[sim] <- sum(simulated_demand > available_stock)
  }
  
  return(oos_results)
}

# Simulate 1000 simulations

6.3 Simulation for lost sales and Overstock

simulate_sales_and_overstock <- function(df, simulations = 1000) {
  lost_sales_results <- numeric(simulations)
  overstock_results <- numeric(simulations)
  
  for (sim in 1:simulations) {
    simulated_demand <- numeric(nrow(df))
    
    for (i in seq_len(nrow(df))) {
      dist <- df$distribution[i]
      
      if (dist == "Poisson") {
        simulated_demand[i] <- rpois(1, lambda = df$lambda[i])
        
      } else if (dist == "Mixture of Binomials") {
        k <- df$k[i]
        q <- df$q_binomial[i]
        p <- df$p_binomial[i]
        simulated_demand[i] <- if (runif(1) < q) {
          rbinom(1, size = k, prob = p)
        } else {
          rbinom(1, size = k + 1, prob = p)
        }
        
      } else if (dist == "Mixture of Negative Binomials") {
        k <- df$k[i]
        q <- df$q_neg_binomial[i]
        p <- df$p_neg_binomial[i]
        mu <- df$Mean_Demand[i]
        simulated_demand[i] <- if (runif(1) < q) {
          rnbinom(1, size = k, mu = mu)
        } else {
          rnbinom(1, size = k + 1, mu = mu)
        }
        
      } else if (dist == "Mixture of Geometrics") {
        p1 <- df$p1_geom[i]
        p2 <- df$p2_geom[i]
        q1 <- df$q1_geom[i]
        q2 <- df$q2_geom[i]
        mix_draw <- runif(1)
        simulated_demand[i] <- if (mix_draw < q1) {
          rgeom(1, prob = p1)
        } else {
          rgeom(1, prob = p2)
        }
        
      } else {
        stop(paste("Unknown distribution:", dist))
      }
    }
    
    available_stock <- df$Stock + df$Open_Order_Qty + df$allocated
    lost_sales_results[sim] <- sum(pmax(0, simulated_demand - available_stock))
    overstock_results[sim] <- sum(pmax(0, available_stock - simulated_demand))
  }
  
  return(list(lost_sales = lost_sales_results, overstock = overstock_results))
}

6.3.1 Simulation for lost sales and overstock per store

simulate_sales_and_overstock_per_store <- function(df, simulations = 1000) {
  lost_sales_results <- matrix(0, nrow = nrow(df), ncol = simulations)
  overstock_results <- matrix(0, nrow = nrow(df), ncol = simulations)
  
  for (sim in 1:simulations) {
    simulated_demand <- numeric(nrow(df))
    
    for (i in seq_len(nrow(df))) {
      dist <- df$distribution[i]
      
      if (dist == "Poisson") {
        simulated_demand[i] <- rpois(1, lambda = df$lambda[i])
        
      } else if (dist == "Mixture of Binomials") {
        k <- df$k[i]
        q <- df$q_binomial[i]
        p <- df$p_binomial[i]
        simulated_demand[i] <- if (runif(1) < q) {
          rbinom(1, size = k, prob = p)
        } else {
          rbinom(1, size = k + 1, prob = p)
        }
        
      } else if (dist == "Mixture of Negative Binomials") {
        k <- df$k[i]
        q <- df$q_neg_binomial[i]
        p <- df$p_neg_binomial[i]
        mu <- df$Mean_Demand[i]
        simulated_demand[i] <- if (runif(1) < q) {
          rnbinom(1, size = k, mu = mu)
        } else {
          rnbinom(1, size = k + 1, mu = mu)
        }
        
      } else if (dist == "Mixture of Geometrics") {
        p1 <- df$p1_geom[i]
        p2 <- df$p2_geom[i]
        q1 <- df$q1_geom[i]
        q2 <- df$q2_geom[i]
        mix_draw <- runif(1)
        simulated_demand[i] <- if (mix_draw < q1) {
          rgeom(1, prob = p1)
        } else {
          rgeom(1, prob = p2)
        }
        
      } else {
        stop(paste("Unknown distribution:", dist))
      }
    }
    
    available_stock <- df$Stock + df$Open_Order_Qty + df$allocated
    lost_sales_results[, sim] <- pmax(0, simulated_demand - available_stock)
    overstock_results[, sim] <- pmax(0, available_stock - simulated_demand)
  }
  
  avg_lost_sales_per_store <- rowMeans(lost_sales_results)
  avg_overstock_per_store <- rowMeans(overstock_results)
  combined_results <- avg_overstock_per_store - avg_lost_sales_per_store
  
  return(data.frame(
    Store_ID = df$Store_ID,
    Avg_Lost_Sales = avg_lost_sales_per_store,
    Avg_Overstock = avg_overstock_per_store,
    Combined_Result = combined_results
  ))
}

7.2 Range of Coverage

simulate_days_until_stockout <- function(df, simulations = 1000, n_days = 79) {
  days_to_stockout <- matrix(NA, nrow = nrow(df), ncol = simulations)
  
  for (i in seq_len(nrow(df))) {
    for (sim in 1:simulations) {
      stock_left <- df$Stock[i] + df$Open_Order_Qty[i] + df$allocated[i]
      day <- 0
      
      while (stock_left > 0) {
        day <- day + 1
        
        dist <- df$distribution[i]
        
        demand <- switch(dist,
          "Poisson" = rpois(1, lambda = df$lambda[i] / n_days),
          "Mixture of Binomials" = {
            k <- df$k[i] / n_days
            k <- max(1, round(k))
            q <- df$q_binomial[i]
            p <- df$p_binomial[i]
            if (runif(1) < q) rbinom(1, k, p) else rbinom(1, k + 1, p)
          },
          "Mixture of Negative Binomials" = {
            k <- df$k[i] / n_days
            k <- max(1, round(k))
            q <- df$q_neg_binomial[i]
            p <- df$p_neg_binomial[i]
            mu <- df$Mean_Demand[i] / n_days
            if (runif(1) < q) rnbinom(1, k, mu = mu) else rnbinom(1, k + 1, mu = mu)
          },
          "Mixture of Geometrics" = {
            p1 <- df$p1_geom[i]
            p2 <- df$p2_geom[i]
            q1 <- df$q1_geom[i]
            if (runif(1) < q1) rgeom(1, p1) else rgeom(1, p2)
          },
          stop(paste("Unknown distribution:", dist))
        )
        
        stock_left <- stock_left - demand
      }
      
      days_to_stockout[i, sim] <- day
    }
  }
  
  # Convert matrix to long-format data frame for boxplot
  days_df_long <- as.data.frame(days_to_stockout)
  days_df_long$Store_ID <- df$Store_ID
  days_df_long <- tidyr::pivot_longer(days_df_long, 
                                      cols = -Store_ID, 
                                      names_to = "Simulation", 
                                      values_to = "Days_To_Stockout")
  return(days_df_long)
}

7.2.1 Solution
